The bank shares fell by 12% on Friday, which is the record low level for 14 years.
The value of the shares has declined by two thirds since January.
According to current stock prices, the total market capital value of the group is around EUR 14 billion. However, company directors say this is not accurate.
The management believes the uncertainties overseas - linked to accepting the American package of USD 700 billion - for the fall of Fortis shares.
The stocks showed a slight rise on Monday.
Filip Dierckx was appointed the new Chief Executive Officer of the bank on Friday.
The financial Institute was also seeking private buyers but no substantial offer has been made.
The Belgian government earlier declared that the investors had no reason to worry, they would not lose their money.
No panic has been developed among the bank customers; no bank rush has occurred.
